ser_is_author":false,"tags":["emacs"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/rzdtx8","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/rzdtx8/may_i_recommend_thinking_emacs_as_your"},{"short_id":"ynrwwo","created_at":"2026-05-27T03:13:35.000-05:00","title":"Keyboard latency probe","url":"https://xkqr.org/bellwether/keyboardtest.html","score":20,"flags":0,"comment_count":7,"description":"\u003cp\u003eHello, fellow geeks!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI was working on a side project when I discovered something odd about how keyboards behave. I only have three keyboards myself to test with, so I would like to recruit your help in providing me data from your keyboards.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe link leads to a simple 3.5 minute browser-based test which lets you record response times and tap durations from your keyboard, and then send them to me. If you can take the time out of your day to help me better understand this, I'd greatly appreciate your contribution.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOnce I have enough data, I will naturally share the results of the analysis back with the community. I'd like to also share the raw data, but I haven't yet thought through any potential privacy concerns around this, so I don't yet know if I will.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Hello, fellow geeks!\r\n\r\nI was working on a side project when I discovered something odd about how keyboards behave. I only have three keyboards myself to test with, so I would like to recruit your help in providing me data from your keyboards.\r\n\r\nThe link leads to a simple 3.5 minute browser-based test which lets you record response times and tap durations from your keyboard, and then send them to me. If you can take the time out of your day to help me better understand this, I'd greatly appreciate your contribution.\r\n\r\nOnce I have enough data, I will naturally share the results of the analysis back with the community. I'd like to also share the raw data, but I haven't yet thought through any potential privacy concerns around this, so I don't yet know if I will.","submitter_user":"kqr","user_is_author":true,"tags":["ask","hardware"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ynrwwo","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ynrwwo/keyboard_latency_probe"},{"short_id":"cmsgwo","created_at":"2026-05-27T02:32:12.000-05:00","title":"CVE-2026-48710 Starlette Host-Header Auth Bypass","url":"https://badhost.org","score":8,"flags":0,"comment_count":5,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"hoistbypetard","user_is_author":false,"tags":["python","web"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/cmsgwo","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/cmsgwo/cve_2026_48710_starlette_host_header_auth"},{"short_id":"ffs7xz","created_at":"2026-05-27T00:53:58.000-05:00","title":"Rethinking the GNOME clipboard issues","url":"https://edu4rdshl.dev/posts/rethinking-the-gnome-clipboard-issues/","score":10,"flags":3,"comment_count":5,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"edu4rdshl","user_is_author":true,"tags":["vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ffs7xz","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ffs7xz/rethinking_gnome_clipboard_issues"},{"short_id":"2jdvxa","created_at":"2026-05-27T00:40:47.000-05:00","title":"What are some of your favourite developer tools?","url":"","score":80,"flags":0,"comment_count":126,"description":"\u003cp\u003eDevelopers are so opinionated that it's difficult to pin down one favourite tool !\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Developers are so opinionated that it's difficult to pin down one favourite tool !","submitter_user":"dhruvp","user_is_author":true,"tags":["ask","programming"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/2jdvxa","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/2jdvxa/what_are_some_your_favourite_developer"},{"short_id":"sgqbvg","created_at":"2026-05-26T22:21:37.000-05:00","title":"Build System Reworked","url":"https://ziglang.org/devlog/2026/#2026-05-26","score":48,"flags":0,"comment_count":9,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_